variable_description: The performance ([1 - breaches]/attendances) calculated for the whole of England.
The month that this activity relates to, stored as a date (1st of each month).
The department type for this activity.
V4: other: Other types of A&E/minor injury activity with designated accommodation for the reception of accident and emergency patients.
1: Emergency departments are a consultant-led 24-hour service with full resuscitation facilities and designated accommodation for the reception of accident and emergency patients.
2: Consultant-led mono speciality accident and emergency service (e.g. ophthalmology, dental) with designated accommodation for the reception of patients.
